[{"location":"#UnitfulLsqFit","page":"UnitfulLsqFit","title":"UnitfulLsqFit","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"UnitfulLsqFit","title":"UnitfulLsqFit","text":"Least squares fitting for Unitful quantities.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"UnitfulLsqFit","title":"UnitfulLsqFit","text":"using Unitful\nusing LsqFit, Latexify, Plots\nusing UnitfulLsqFit, UnitfulLatexify, UnitfulRecipes\ndefault(;fontfamily=\"Computer Modern\")\n\nlength = 1000\n@. model(x, p) = p[1] + p[2]*exp(-((x-p[3])/p[4])^2) + p[5]*x\np0 = [\n        2.0u\"m/s\", # y offset\n        10.2u\"m/s\", # peak height\n        -1.0u\"s\", # x offset\n        0.6u\"s\", # peak width\n        1.2u\"m/s^2\", # slope\n     ]\nt = range(-5, 5; length)u\"s\"\nv = model(t, p0) + randn(length)*u\"m/s\" # noisy signal\nfit = curve_fit(model, t, v, [0.0u\"m/s\", 1.0u\"m/s\", 0.0u\"s\", 1.0u\"s\", 1.0u\"m/s^2\"])\nmdtable([p0 fit.param];head=latexraw.([:Truth, :Fit]))","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"UnitfulLsqFit","title":"UnitfulLsqFit","text":"plot(t, v; st=:scatter, label=\"Samples\")\nplot!(t,model(t, fit.param);\n         linewidth=2, label=\"Fit\",\n         xguide=\"t\", yguide=\"v\", unitformat=(l,u)->\"\\$$l / $(latexraw(u))\\$\", legend=-45,\n     )\nsavefig(\"1.svg\") # hide\nnothing # hide","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"UnitfulLsqFit","title":"UnitfulLsqFit","text":"(Image: )","category":"page"},{"location":"#Warning-concerning-exponential-fits","page":"UnitfulLsqFit","title":"Warning concerning exponential fits","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"UnitfulLsqFit","title":"UnitfulLsqFit","text":"Consider the function y(x) = x^p. If you know the dimension of y and x, and neither of them is unitless, there is exactly one choice of p that allows this comparison â€“ and any adjacent p^* will not only make the comparison inaccurate but impossible. Curve fitting in this case doesn't make sense, and will most likely simply fail with UnitfulLsqFit. The dimensionality of the edxpression can not be determined by the values of the fit parameters.","category":"page"}]
